headline: Why Wynn Resorts (WYNN) Stock Is Down Today
summary: Shares of luxury hotels and casino operator Wynn Resorts (NASDAQ:WYNN) fell 7.8% in the morning session after China imposed a 34% tariff on all U.S. imports amid escalating trade war tensions. This was partly in response to the "reciprocal tariffs" announced by the Trump administration the previous day, with levies on Chinese goods estimated to be as high as 50%.
